## AI model storage

Trained models are saved under **`models/`** (gitignored except `.gitkeep`). Docker mounts `./models:/app/models` so files persist on EC2 across rebuilds.

```bash
# Train from recent Binance klines + backtest labels
python -m core.main train-ai --symbol BTCUSDT --symbol ETHUSDT --timeframe 15m

# Enable filter in .env after training
AI_FILTER_ENABLED=true
```

API: `GET /api/v1/ai/models`, `POST /api/v1/ai/train`, `POST /api/v1/ai/reload`

**Weekly auto-retrain:** `.github/workflows/retrain-ai.yml` (Sundays 02:00 UTC) runs `scripts/ec2-retrain-ai.sh` on EC2. Manual: GitHub → Actions → Retrain AI Model → Run workflow.

Active model path: `AI_MODEL_PATH=models/trade_filter.joblib` (default)

## User preferences — enable / disable via chat (not dashboard)

**Local storage:** `.cursor/rules/aibottrade-preferences.local.mdc` (gitignored)

The user controls features by asking the agent (e.g. *"enable AI filter on live"*, *"disable AI filter"*). The agent must:

1. Update toggles in `aibottrade-preferences.local.mdc`
2. Apply on EC2 and/or local (`.env` + `config/default.yaml`)
3. `sudo docker compose up -d --force-recreate bot` on EC2 (or restart local API)

### Current toggles (see preferences file for live values)

| Feature | Preference key | EC2 files when enabled |
|---------|----------------|------------------------|
| AI filter in trades | `use_in_trades` | `.env`: `AI_FILTER_ENABLED=true`, `default.yaml`: `ai_filter.enabled: true` |
| AI min confidence | `min_confidence` | `default.yaml`: `ai_filter.min_confidence` |
| Weekly retrain | `scheduled` | GitHub workflow only — no runtime toggle |

**Do not** ask the user to use the dashboard for these toggles unless they prefer it.

